12/12/2022, 09:06 - Duncan: Joe the Snake slithered up to the Wordle board,
His beady eyes fixed on the jumbled letters hoard.
He'd heard that Wordle was the game to beat,
And Joe was determined to cheat and cheat.

He whispered words to his friends in the grass,
But they quickly scattered, too afraid to last.
Joe thought he had the game all sewn up,
But he hadn't reckoned on the Wordle judge's sharp eyes and pluck.

The judge was handsome and wise as an owl,
And he spotted Joe's cheating in a single scowl.
He called out Joe and asked him to explain,
But Joe just coiled and hissed in vain.

The judge declared Joe the loser fair and square,
And Joe slithered off in shame and despair.
He'd thought he was sly, but he was just a snake,
And at Wordle, he was nothing but fake.

23/07/2024, 09:49 - Duncan: Wordlers! I've looked back through the chat and can't see this mentioned in detail...

You may not know that for the past year our very own Super-Claire has been diligently completing Wordle whilst casually walking the entire UK coastal path!

This amazing journey of 5000+ miles is in support of two homelessness charities and is due to be completed _this_ Saturday. What an incredible inspiration!

Please donate if you can and share to friends, family, work and loose acquaintances to help smash the £25k goal - Woohoo!!!

https://www.justgiving.com/team/claires-great-british-walk

https://www.instagram.com/clairesgreatbritishwalk/

21/02/2025, 22:01 - Duncan: Game Preview: Weekly Finale Showdown
The final game of the week is upon us, and the field is set for a thrilling contest. With six recent performances to assess, the form guide suggests a tight battle at the top—but will class shine through, or could we see a surprise winner?

The Favourite – Al
Al heads into this contest as the clear market leader, boasting the lowest average finishing score (3.67) across his last six outings. A model of consistency, he’s shown a strong ability to recover from mid-week setbacks and find his stride when it matters. If he can replicate that form today, he’ll be hard to peg back. The bookies have him as the one to beat, and rightly so.

The Challengers – Snakey & Pete
Snakey and Pete are neck-and-neck in the betting, with identical average scores (3.83). Both have demonstrated solid reliability, staying in touch with the leaders without necessarily dominating. Snakey’s strength lies in his ability to grind out performances, while Pete has flashes of brilliance but will need to find more consistency to threaten Al.

Lively Outsiders – Claire & Rob
Claire and Rob have been hit-and-miss this week, averaging 4.33 across their games. They’ve had their moments but will need a standout game to upset the more consistent market leaders. That said, with a bit of luck, they could sneak into the places and offer some each-way value.

Verdict:
Al is the standout selection here and fully deserves favouritism. His track record suggests he’s the most dependable performer in the field, and if he plays to form, the others will be scrapping for the minor placings. Snakey and Pete are the biggest dangers and could offer better value if the odds drift.

For those looking for a speculative punt, Claire and Rob have outside chances of sneaking into the frame—but they’ll really need things to go their way.
